08/07/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Zeljko Komsic assumed the rotating chairmanship of the tripartite BiH Presidency from Serb member Nebojsa Radmanovic on Friday (July 6th).
Komsic, a Croat, will be at the helm for the next eight months.
In other news, High Representative to BiH Miroslav Lajcak met in Sarajevo with representatives of the Srebrenica and Zepa Enclaves' Mothers association on Saturday.
He said full justice must be established regarding the 1995 Srebrenica massacre, but voiced opposition to demands to remove Srebrenica from Republika Srpska's jurisdiction and give it special status.
(Nezavisne Novine, Dnevni Avaz - 08/07/07;
RTRS, Srna, PBS BiH - 06/07/07)
